-- RadioShack Cycling Team Drops Frank Schleck as Doping Ban Ends
-- B y   A l e x   D u f f
-- 2013-07-04T16:42:02Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-07-04/radioshack-cycling-team-drops-frank-schleck-as-doping-ban-ends.html
The RadioShack-Leopard cycling team
said it won’t offer another contract to  Frank Schleck , who is
nearing the end of a one-year ban for failing a drugs test.  Schleck’s younger brother, Andy, is the lead rider on the
team, which is competing at the Tour de France. Team sponsor
Trek Bicycle Corp. will take over the squad after this season.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Alex Duff at 
 aduff4@bloomberg.net  